 <H1>SQL is More Than Just a Query Language</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Data-definition language (DDL):
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Create / destroy / alter relations and views.
<LI>Define integrity constraints (IC’s).
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Update language:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Insert /delete / modify (update) tuples.
<LI>Interact closely with ICs.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Access Control:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Can grant / revoke the right to access and manipulate tables (relations / views).</UL></UL></P>
